I’m afraid that I gotta take my 4 stars down to 3 for now... We’ve just loved dining at Craft since they opened a few years ago. Our ‘Go To’ pizza & salad in the ‘hood. But that was in the days b4 the Age of COVID. We’ve been carrying out from Craft pretty frequently the past few months, and I’d have to say that the pizza has not been as good. We’ve been increasingly disappointed. The sauce is still spectacular... still fresh, quality ingredients, but seems like far less cheese & toppings, usually in clumps and not distributed evenly. The crust is still good, but seems sloppily prepared, it’s inconsistent in thickness and sticks mercilessly to the box. The champagne vinaigrette is still awesome! But less variety of mixed greens and other fixins’. I know you’re busy, don’t rush it and be so sloppy, slow down and do it right. You are slightly higher in price than other pizza joints in the ‘hood, but we’re willing to pay for quality. We love your staff, but we’re gonna make a switch back to some of the olde standards in the ‘hood for a while... We’ll likely be back to check in, but there is a lot of good pizza to be had in Chicago.

Craft Pizza is slightly off the beaten path on a quiet stretch of Damen just west of the heart of Wicker Park.  The layout of the restaurant is similar to the previous resident.  The kitchen is out in the open behind a counter and there is limited seating.  The pizza is thin crust and you've got a ton of choices to choose from.  All ingredients are of the highest quality and the pizza is tasty.  I wished the crust had slightly more flavor and were a little easier on the chew.  It's a very good pie and I'll definitely return.  Here's a big plus... it's BYOB.  If you're willing to make the short walk and save a few bucks on drink, skip the hour long wait at Piece and go to Craft Pizza.  (you may still have to wait but it should be shorter).
